        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 2:47PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles northwest of Roswell, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 50 mph, and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of North Central Chaves County.

This includes Highway 285 between Mile Markers 121 and 140.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
